Crucible12 is a hardware-tuned local-inference stack and setup automation
layer. It does not vendor, fork, or modify any of the projects below — they
are installed as ordinary dependencies and configured via the files in
config/ and setup/.

- OpenCode — the coding agent itself. https://github.com/anomalyco/opencode
  MIT License, Copyright (c) Anomaly Co.
- llama.cpp — local inference engine. https://github.com/ggml-org/llama.cpp
  MIT License, Copyright (c) Georgi Gerganov and contributors.
- Qwen3-Coder-Next and Qwen3-Coder-30B-A3B-Instruct — Qwen Team / Alibaba Cloud.
  See respective Hugging Face model cards for license terms.
- GGUF quantizations used by default are produced by Unsloth
  (https://huggingface.co/unsloth).

Crucible12's own scripts, configs, and documentation are MIT-licensed — see
LICENSE.
